    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - REMOVE - OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Engage two (2) mainshaft sliding clutches into two (2) mainshaft gears to lock the
                transmission (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301719">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301719" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301719" filename="../figg13/G1301719.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Output/Yoke Companion Flange</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a large breaker bar or air impact wrench to remove the output shaft nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301720">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301720" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301720" filename="../figg13/G1301720.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Remove Output Shaft Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the yoke or flange straight to the rear and off the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301721">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301721" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301721" filename="../figg13/G1301721.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Pull Yoke To Rear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
